Watch this user's images. They are on a firebase ref /userImages.
- db.ref('userImages').child(user.id).on('value', snap => this.userImages = snap.val())
They will be used for displaying user's uploaded images.
The url for these can be retrived from firebase storage, using image name and user id-
- storage.ref(`${userId}/${imageName}`).getUrl() //for each
The image names will be used as options for which image a spot shall have.
- <option v-for="image in userImages" value="image.name" label="image.name" />

VIEW FOR UPLOADING A NEW IMAGE WITH NEW NAME
